Have you ever wondered what heaven looks like? Or hell for that matter? So, you may beleive that it's made up, or either one of them don't exiswt, but you must have some idea even if (in your opinion) it's just a story. I don't beleive in heaven, but i do have an image of it if i were to draw in on a peice of paper. It'd be situated in a bundle of soft, cut cirrus clouds, abandoned in the colour of the most beatiful blue sky. There'd be glorious golden gates sectioning it off from the rest of the sky. And there'd be people walking around, barefoot, in luxurious white togas. And everywhere you went, there'd be a peaceful choir of cherubs singing away in the background. There'd be not hate or anger, just love, tranquil and harmony. Ok, so it's not exactly my way of life, but it's what i'd prefer if i was ever to end up there. Hell, however, that's another story...

I really hate it when my toothbrush goes missing. This usually occurs when i sleep at someones house and leave it there, or don't get around to taking it out of my bag. It's not laziness, it just puts me off, letting the now putrid rod make contact with my cleany teeth. So when this happens, i have to use my mums or something.

D'ya know what i could watch right now? Star Wars. Yeah, yeah, i've seen them all a dozen times before, but i just finnished watching the Family Guy spoof version of it and it really got me in the mood for watching it. Cat and Alex told me that the word 'Ewok' isn't even mentioned in 'The Empire Strikes Back'. I don't beleive them. I think i'll have to go and check that one.

Is it just me, or does anyone else think that Dave Grohl is a god among men? Well, i for one sure as hell do! Me and Cat were talking about this the other day, if you ruled the world, whom would be your manslaves? I said Dave straight away. And Taylor Hawkins. And Matt Tuck. And Billy Joe Armstong. And Jeff Hardy. And Milo Ventimiglia. Ahh, well. A girl can dream...

My fave was when i had an awesome day out with my friends, Danny, Alex, Cat, Josh and Emma. We had been walking home from Stanley park after a vicious and long-lasting game of manhunt, and it was after dark. We were all just walking arm in arm eating haribo and exchanging small-talk as we were all absolutley knackered. All of a sudden, Danny wizzed infront of us and took a shot. Aren't ipods just the most prettiest little things in the whole damn world? Some people may agree, some will not. However, i've always adored them and all i got is a shitty lil' ipod shuffle. Sounds great, you think, but let me expand. I have the original shuffle. Crud! Why couldn't i have waited for the mini, coloured clip-on version? Sure, that'd be about a year and a 1/2, but it's an utter downer! Alex, my current boyfriend has just received the new nano for christmas and to be honest, the original nano is a much better design, but it's better than what i've got! Anyway i'd better quit whining...Here's the pic:

i've seen all of these icon making comptitions everywhere and  i don't know if i want to join them or not. Its not because i think i'm bad at making them or anything, its just that i'm new to LJ so, i'm a bit shy of talking to other users. Sounds stupid but next time i find a good competiton, i'm going to make them and post them on my own site, instead of competing for them on someone elses. Hope thats ok with everyone :)

How did you spend summers when you were a kid?

Me, my brother and my dad used to go to the beach and spend the whole day there. We would walk up to the sand dunes, get a Notrianni ice cram and go to some quaint cafe in St.Annes. Then we would walk back along the beach, collecting shells and playing in the sea. 
I sometimes went shopping with my friends and had girly sleepovers. You know, a chick flick and some nail varnish! The next day, we would go ice skating. One time, we were supposed to met at the cinema to watch Mr. Bean's holiday, and Laura didn't turn up. So me, Amy, Emma and Abby went on th promnade and got a horse and carriage ride. Then we went to Kingscote feild and messed about. Ahhhhhh... those were the days...

Finally!  I got my journal colours just the way i wanted them!... OKAYYYYYYYY So i need a bit of help adding pics and what not, coz i don't know how to do them yet. Now, if you don't mind, i think i'm going to go d
downstairs and watch hot fuzz!

Hi, i'm new to the whole livejournal thing. So i don't really know what i'm doing! I've seen some fab Jeff Hardy communities about and thats where i got inspiration to join. I'm still shocked over benoits death. I don't think that anyone should suddenly lose respect for him because of what he has done. He truly was a great wrestler and brought loads to the industry of WWE. *Eyes are filling up*. Anyway, I'm not realy miffed about the Hardys losing at Vengeance, because i  heared that they want to focus on being single competitors. Hope jeff gets a belt though, like the intercontinental, again.
